	<key>readme</key>
	<string>On my pull request reviews, I have a color system. I do this so that I can more easily convey to you where a comment is on the scale of "FYI" to "Hard No". This allows me to provide insight and feedback without unnecessarily stopping progress.

"Passing" (green with a check mark) means the comment is very non-blocking. On the scale, this goes from `FYI` to `keep going, but in a future change, could you please address this?`.

"Optional" (blue with an info mark) means the comment is still non-blocking, but I have an opinion on why you might not want to merge it as-is. On the scale, this is `What if…` to `Are you sure you meant to do this? If you meant to, it's totally acceptable, but I'm not sure you meant to`.

"Blocking" (red with an X mark) means the comment is blocking. On the scale, this goes from `Hey, let's talk about this before we move forward` to `AAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHH!!!!!`.</string>
